<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key C, melody in Dm (Dorian/Aeolian mode). Medieval Communion hymn.
- LH: Dm D2-A2-D3-F3; F F2-C3-F3-A3; Am A2-E3-A3-C4; Gm G2-D3-G3-Bb3.
- A major (III in Dm) used as leading-tone chord: A2-E3-A3-C#4.
- Bb chromaticism (bar 6,7,12) darkens the modal color appropriately.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- A/C# secondary dominant to Dm creates tension-resolution pattern
- Bars 6-7: Bb-F-Gm-C cadence providing IV-bVII-III area motion
- Contrary motion throughout: melody descends, bass rises

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening: Dm tonic, sparse two-note RH
- Middle: Bb/F/Gm area for modal richness
- Climax bars 11-12: high register F5, D5
- Final: Pure Dm close bar 15
-->
